and it'll never get any smaller.

01:02:41.335 --> 01:02:43.628
-lsn't that neat?
-lt's like gum.

01:02:44.213 --> 01:02:46.714
No. Gum is for chewing.

01:02:46.882 --> 01:02:49.175
If you tried chewing
one of these Gobstoppers...

01:02:49.343 --> 01:02:51.386
...you'd break all your little teeth off.

01:02:51.553 --> 01:02:53.888
But they sure do taste terrific.

01:03:01.105 --> 01:03:03.564
And this is Hair Toffee.

01:03:03.732 --> 01:03:06.067
You suck down one of
these little boogers...

01:03:06.235 --> 01:03:08.152
...and in exactly half an hour...

01:03:08.362 --> 01:03:12.073
...a brand-new crop of hair will grow out
over the top of your little noggin.

01:03:12.241 --> 01:03:14.450
And a mustache. And a beard.

01:03:14.618 --> 01:03:17.161
-Who wants a beard?
-Well...

01:03:17.371 --> 01:03:20.498
...beatniks, for one.
Folk singers and motorbike riders.

01:03:20.666 --> 01:03:24.794
You know, all those hip, jazzy,
super-cool, neat, keen and groovy cats.

01:03:24.962 --> 01:03:27.463
It's in the fridge, daddy-o.
Are you hep to the jive?

01:03:27.631 --> 01:03:29.716
Can you dig what I'm laying down?
I knew you could.

01:03:29.883 --> 01:03:32.510
Slide me some skin, soul brother.

01:03:35.723 --> 01:03:37.724
Unfortunately,
the mixture isn't right yet.

01:03:37.891 --> 01:03:41.185
Because an Oompa-Loompa
tried some yesterday, and, well, he--

01:03:46.025 --> 01:03:47.191
How are you today?

01:03:48.986 --> 01:03:50.403
You look great.

01:03:59.079 --> 01:04:00.538
Watch this.

01:04:00.748 --> 01:04:02.999
[ALARM WAILING]

01:04:29.026 --> 01:04:30.276
You mean that's it?

01:04:30.778 --> 01:04:32.695
Do you even know what "it" is?

01:04:33.072 --> 01:04:35.073
-lt's gum.
-Yeah.

01:04:35.240 --> 01:04:39.243
It's a stick of the most amazing and
sensational gum in the whole universe.

01:04:39.453 --> 01:04:41.579
Know why? Know why?

01:04:41.747 --> 01:04:44.999
Because this gum is a full
three-course dinner all by itself.

01:04:45.167 --> 01:04:46.751
[TlTTERS]

01:04:48.295 --> 01:04:49.754
Why would anyone want that?

01:04:57.137 --> 01:04:59.639
"It will be the end of all kitchens
and all cooking.

01:04:59.807 --> 01:05:03.518
Just a little strip of Wonka's magic
chewing gum and that is all you will...

01:05:03.685 --> 01:05:05.812
...ever need at breakfast,
lunch and dinner.

01:05:05.979 --> 01:05:10.400
This piece of gum happens to be tomato
soup, roast beef and blueberry pie."

01:05:10.567 --> 01:05:12.485
It sounds great.

01:05:12.986 --> 01:05:16.114
-lt sounds weird.
-lt sounds like my kind of gum.

01:05:18.992 --> 01:05:21.911
I'd rather you didn't.
There are still some things that are--

01:05:22.079 --> 01:05:25.498
I'm the world-record holder in
chewing gum. l'm not afraid of anything.

01:05:31.088 --> 01:05:34.173
-How is it, honey?
-lt's amazing!

01:05:34.341 --> 01:05:36.968
Tomato soup.
I can feel it running down my throat.

01:05:37.136 --> 01:05:38.594
Yeah. Spit it out.

01:05:38.762 --> 01:05:41.305
-Young lady, l think you'd better--
-lt's changing.

01:05:42.057 --> 01:05:44.308
Roast beef, with baked potato.

01:05:44.643 --> 01:05:47.311
-Crispy skin and butter.
-Keep chewing.

01:05:47.521 --> 01:05:50.815
My little girl's gonna be the first person
to have a chewing-gum meal.

01:05:51.024 --> 01:05:53.443
Yeah. l'm just a little concerned
about the--

01:05:53.610 --> 01:05:55.278
Blueberry pie and ice cream!

01:05:55.863 --> 01:05:58.364
-That part.
-What's happening to her nose?

01:06:04.037 --> 01:06:05.329
It's turning blue.

01:06:08.208 --> 01:06:09.959
Your whole nose has gone purple.

01:06:10.544 --> 01:06:12.545
What do you mean?

01:06:13.172 --> 01:06:15.882
Violet, you're turning violet.

01:06:16.925 --> 01:06:20.511
-What's happening?
-l told you l hadn't quite got it right.

01:06:20.679 --> 01:06:23.723
Because it goes a little funny
when it gets to the dessert.

01:06:23.891 --> 01:06:25.600
It's the blueberry pie that does it.

01:06:26.393 --> 01:06:28.561
I'm terribly sorry.

01:06:37.196 --> 01:06:40.573
Mother? What's happening to me?

01:06:53.295 --> 01:06:54.712
She's swelling up.

01:06:58.842 --> 01:07:00.092
Like a blueberry.

01:07:28.830 --> 01:07:32.875
I've tried it on, like, 20 Oompa-Loompas,
and each one ended up as a blueberry.

01:07:33.043 --> 01:07:34.835
It's just weird.

01:07:35.003 --> 01:07:37.004
But l can't have a blueberry
as a daughter.

01:07:37.172 --> 01:07:38.756
How is she supposed to compete?

01:07:38.924 --> 01:07:40.341
You could put her in a county fair.

01:07:44.721 --> 01:07:46.180
[ALARM BLARES NOTE]

